      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-sqa",
      "rationale": "The FEA solver (Abaqus 2022) is operated under a documented software quality assurance plan conforming to FDA 21 CFR Part 820 and ISO 13485. Version control, change management, and validation testing logs are archived. Regression test suite of 47 benchmark cases executed at each release; all pass within specified tolerances. Achieved level 3 exceeds the required level 2 for MRL 3 Class II device."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-ncv",
      "rationale": "Numerical code verification performed using NAFEMS benchmark problems LE1, LE3, and LE10 for linear elasticity and the Abaqus built-in patch test suite. All benchmark results agree with analytical solutions to within 0.5%. Manufacturer verification documentation reviewed and found complete. Achieved level 3 satisfies the required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-de",
      "rationale": "Mesh convergence study conducted with four systematically refined meshes (element edge lengths 4 mm, 2 mm, 1 mm, 0.5 mm) using C3D10 tetrahedral elements. Richardson extrapolation applied; grid convergence index (GCI) for peak von Mises stress is 1.8%, below the 5% acceptance threshold. Production mesh at 1 mm global / 0.25 mm local refinement in stress concentration regions. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-tc",
      "rationale": "Bench-top testing conducted under ISO 14243-1 and ISO 14243-3 protocols with full documentation of load profiles, displacement constraints, tibio-femoral contact geometry, and environmental conditions (37°C saline bath). Load application fixtures calibrated to NIST-traceable standards. Five independent specimen replicates tested; test conditions replicated in the FEA boundary conditions with documented correspondence. Achieved level 4 exceeds required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-oc",
      "rationale": "Quantitative output comparison performed for three quantities of interest: peak von Mises stress (4.2% mean relative error), maximum principal strain (5.1% mean relative error), and fatigue life (factor 1.8 vs. experimental median). All metrics satisfy pre-specified acceptance criteria. Statistical comparison accounts for inter-specimen variability using a two-sided 95% confidence interval. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-rqoi",
      "rationale": "The quantities of interest (peak von Mises stress, maximum principal strain, fatigue life index) are directly linked to the clinical failure mode of tibial tray fracture and the regulatory submission requirement for fatigue endurance demonstration. A formal QoI relevance matrix maps each computational output to a specific clinical risk and regulatory criterion, reviewed and approved by the credibility assessment team. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-rva",
      "rationale": "Validation activities use the same tibial tray geometry (production CAD), same CoCrMo alloy material, and loading profiles derived from ISO 14243-3 which represent the in vivo gait cycle envelope. A validation relevance assessment document formally scores similarity across geometry, material, loading, and boundary conditions dimensions, concluding high relevance. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-nse",
      "rationale": "Iterative solver convergence monitored via force and displacement residual norms; convergence criterion set at 1e-6 relative norm. All load increments converge within 15 iterations. No spurious hourglassing or locking artefacts observed in element energy checks. Nonlinear contact iterations converge monotonically. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-ue",
      "rationale": "Model setup and execution performed by two independent analysts following a documented simulation procedure. Independent review of mesh, boundary conditions, material assignments, and load step definitions completed prior to production runs. Discrepancies resolved via adjudication; final model configuration signed off by lead engineer. Achieved level 2 meets required level 2."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-mf",
      "rationale": "Linear elastic constitutive model selected based on literature evidence that CoCrMo tibial trays operate well below yield under ISO 14243 loading (maximum computed strain 0.08%, yield strain ~0.45%). Model form uncertainty quantified by comparing linear elastic predictions against an elastoplastic simulation for worst-case loading; difference in peak stress 2.3%. Bone-implant interface modeled as fully bonded, justified by cemented fixation protocol. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-mi",
      "rationale": "Material properties (E = 210 GPa, ν = 0.30, ultimate tensile strength 900 MPa) sourced from ASTM F1537 and confirmed by coupon testing of production-batch material. Geometric inputs derived from production CAD with dimensional inspection report. Loading inputs from ISO 14243-3 standard gait cycle; sensitivity analysis conducted across ±15% load variation showing peak stress variation of ±6.3%. Input uncertainty propagated via Monte Carlo sampling (n=500). Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-ts",
      "rationale": "Ten tibial tray specimens from three production lots used for validation testing. Specimens dimensionally inspected (CMM) and material certified per ASTM F1537. Sample size justified by statistical power analysis targeting 80% power to detect a 10% difference in peak stress at α=0.05. Lot-to-lot variability assessed and found within specification. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "https://uofa.net/synth/acceptance/nagaraja-cou1-ortho-ac-eip",
      "rationale": "Formal equivalency assessment performed comparing simulation input parameters against bench-test conditions across seven dimensions: geometry, material, loading magnitude, loading waveform, boundary conditions, environmental conditions, and fixation method. Each dimension scored using a structured equivalency rubric; all seven dimensions rated equivalent or conservatively bounding. Documented in Equivalency Assessment Report EAR-2026-001. Achieved level 3 meets required level 3."
    }
